    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1879-08-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1879-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="482"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d482">
                <head>No. 450.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lowell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1879-08-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 22, 1879</date>. (Received September
                        10.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 196.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my dispatch No. 146, I have now the
                    honor to inclose herewith a copy and translation of a note from the minister of
                    state, informing me that the excess of tonnage dues exacted at Manila from the
                    American vessels Bullion, Frank Lambeth, Washington, Henry A. Litchfield, and
                    Stephen, has been ordered to be returned to the consignees of said vessels.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. R. LOWELL.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No 196—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Duke of Tetuan</gloss> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Lowell</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ministry of State</hi>
                            </placeName>,<lb/>
                            <date calendar="gregorian" when="1879-07-31">
                                <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 31, 1879</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>; I have the honor to make known to your
                        excellency, referring to the affair which occasioned your note of the 30th
                        December last, as to the arrival at Manila of the vessels Bullion, Frank
                        Lambeth, Washington, Henry A. Litchfield, and Stephen, that the minister of
                        ultramar informs me that he has ordered the restitution of the additional
                        sum collected from the consignees of said vessels by exacting tonnage dues
                        according to the number of Spanish tons, instead of those which appeared in
                        the register of each vessel.</p>
                    <p>I avail myself of this opportunity to reiterate to your excellency the
                        assurance of my most distinguished consideration.</p>
                    <closer>The <hi rend="smallcaps">Duke of</hi> TETUAN.</closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
